args:
In the midst of the group's march, Cleo opens
a package given to her by Chelle and finds a
fantastic dress inside. After putting it on,
she allows herself to indulge in a fantasy
of being the daughter in a noble family.
*wheeze* *pant* We've come quite far...\nand I fear I need a rest...
Of course, Cleo. Feel free to rest here.\nI'll come back for you in a bit.
I should have something to eat while I\ncool off. Perhaps there is some food in\nthis package Chelle gave me.
Hmm. If there IS food inside, there must\nbe a lot of it; this package is enormous.
Perhaps it isn't food at all.
Goodness! It's the dress from earlier!\nAnd there seems to be a letter as well...
＂Though this fine dress ill befits you,\nI give it to you as a memento of our\ntime together regardless. - Chelle＂

Heavens, but that woman is a devil;
I am WELL aware it does not suit me!
Still, now that she's given it to me, I
suppose there's no harm in putting it on...
Hmm... Yes, there's nothing wrong with\nthe fit. The problem must simply be\nthat I am not of noble blood.
But suppose I were a sylvan aristocrat?\nWould it suit me then?
If my birth were different, my deportment\nand bearing would be different as well.
Posh, but my days are filled with boredom.\nWhere IS my butler?!
Finally! Now sit there; I would have\nyou distract me from this dull malaise.
Tell me, what do you see on the table\nin front of you there?
An array of food, my lady.\nA full meal, in fact.
Indeed! It is a table groaning under the\nweight of the best and most delicious\ndishes I could conceive of.
You want to take a bite, don't you?!\nYou want to stuff all of this food into\nyour quivering, drool-filled maw!
Ah, but you cannot do so until\nI grant you my permission!
O-of course, my lady. And yet,\nthe aroma is...overwhelming.
You may not eat until I say so!\nSit there and wait like a good butler!\nWaaaaaaaaaait...
NOW you may eat! And once you do,\nI would hear your thoughts so I might\nmake improvements to the recipe.
Er, but if I may, why are you preparing\nmeals yourself? A lady of stature does\nnot normally cook.
I wonder... Are you REALLY a noble?
...Hmm, this is more difficult than\nI thought. My thoughts still default\nto those of a servant.

If I want to do this, I must think
even MORE like classic nobility.
I am better than everyone...
Everyone exists for me alone...

Hmph! You are trash! Odious refuse!
I would have you lick the dirt from my
boots, but that would only make them
even MORE unclean!
How DARE you cavort about MY manor\nand pollute MY sight so shamelessly!
Nothing to say? Rat got your tongue?\nFie, but you ARE trash!
Acknowledge me when I am berating you!\nAdmit what trash you are, trash!\nScrape and grovel before me!
You decline to answer? Fine.\nYou are of use to me no longer.
In fact, I shall dispose of you myself.\nI need only my broom and mop, and—
...Wait, why am I cleaning?\nI'm supposed to be a noble!
That was better, though. I think I'm finally\napproaching the proper mentality.\nSurely THIS time I shall succeed!
Are you rested up, Cleo?\nWe need to be on our way.
Ah, how time flies. Please just give me\na few more moments, if you would?
Um, Cleo? Where'd you get that dress?
Th-this just happened to be in my bag!\nI don't actually LIKE it!
Then why did you put it on...?
You know what? It doesn't matter.\nIt looks great on you regardless.
That is not what I need to hear\nfrom you at the moment!
Ugh. We're leaving. I should have known\nthis entire affair was useless...
